<HEADLINE>
EPA REWARDS 73 FOR REPORTING POLLUTION CASES IN 2006
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Feb. 3 (CNA) 02/03/07  17:52:52 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Environmental Protection Administration (EPA) rewarded 73
people for reporting pollution cases in 2006, an EPA spokesman
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 73 people each won between NT$1,000 and NT$160,000 for a
total amount of NT$2 million (US$61,233) for reporting 38 water
pollution, 22 illegal waste disposal, five air pollution, four
noise pollution, one marine pollution and one drinking water
pollution cases. Two polluters got jail sentences as a result.
</P>
<P>
People who report pollution cases that are verified by the EPA
will be eligible to prizes of up to NT$200,000.
</P>
